President Obama has nominated John Kammerzell, Mark Martinez, and Stephen James Smith to be U.S. Marshals. Kammerzell is nominated for the District of Colorado, Martinez for the District of Nebraska, and Smith for the Southern District of Georgia. All three nominees have a background in law enforcement and have demonstrated dedication to protecting their fellow Americans. Kammerzell is currently the Director of the Colorado Department of Law's Peace Officer Standards and Training Board. Martinez served in the Omaha Police Department for 25 years and is now an adjunct instructor at the University of Nebraska at Omaha. Smith is a 28-year veteran of the Savannah Police Department and has also served as Chief of Police for Thunderbolt, Georgia, and the Memorial Health University Medical Center. He received two Bronze Stars and a Purple Heart for his service in the U.S. Army during the Vietnam War.